<div class="card-header">
<h1>2 Egg Breakfast and Sausage </h1></div>
<p> Growing up, I never knew how to cook. When I finally learned, the easiest thing for me to learn was eggs and sausage. So everytime I cooked breakfast for family I was responsible for the eggs and sausage.
 I usually eat this meal as a quick breakfast option. Today, I will be sharing these ingredients. </p>
  
  <center> <h2 class="card-title"> Ingredients</h2> </center>
<ul>
 <li class="list-group-item">2 eggs</li> 
    <li class="list-group-item">2 tablespoons of butter</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">2 tps of salt</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">2 tsp of pepper</li>
    <li class="list-group-item">13oz Sausage</li>
 
</ul>
  <center> <h2 class="card-title">What To Do</h2> </center>
<ol>
    <li>Turn on the skillet for eggs</li>
    <li> Put 2 Tablespoons of butter in the skillet to melt</li>
    <li>Add 2 eggs to skillet</li>
    <li>Add 2 tsp of salt</li>
    <li>Add 2 tsp of pepper</li>
    <li>While eggs cook, turn on second skillet for sausage</li> 
    <li>Stir the eggs until they begin to scramble</li>
    <li>Turn sausages over until they are brown on both sides</li>  
    <li>Reduce heat, Plate and Serve</li> 
 
    </ol>
    
